**Main Renderer (Lines 174-227):**
```174:227:native/src/tui_app.cpp
    auto component = Renderer([&] {
      // Show setup screen if requested
      if (show_setup_) {
        return RenderSetupScreen(selected_tab);
      }

      // Get snapshot atomically (non-blocking)
      Snapshot snap = GetSnapshot();

      // Always render something - never return empty
      // This ensures the screen is never blank
      auto header = RenderHeader(snap);

      // Render tabs manually (not as Container component)
      std::vector<std::string> tab_names = {
        "Dashboard", "Current Positions", "Historic Positions",
        "Orders", "Alerts"
      };
      Elements tab_elements;
      for (size_t i = 0; i < tab_names.size(); ++i) {
        if (i > 0) tab_elements.push_back(text("  "));
        auto tab_text = text(tab_names[i]);
        if (i == static_cast<size_t>(selected_tab)) {
          tab_text = tab_text | bold | color(Color::Cyan1) | bgcolor(Color::Blue1);
        }
        tab_elements.push_back(tab_text);
      }
      auto tabs_rendered = hbox(tab_elements);

      // Render the selected tab content
      Element content;
      switch (selected_tab) {
        case 0: content = RenderDashboard()->Render(); break;
        case 1: content = RenderPositions()->Render(); break;
        case 2: content = RenderHistoric()->Render(); break;
        case 3: content = RenderOrders()->Render(); break;
        case 4: content = RenderAlerts()->Render(); break;
        default: content = text("Unknown tab"); break;
      }

      auto footer = RenderFooter(selected_tab);

      // Ensure the entire layout fills the screen
      // Use flex on content to fill available vertical space
      return vbox({
        header,
        separator(),
        tabs_rendered,
        separator(),
        content | flex,  // This expands to fill available space
        separator(),
        footer,
      });
    });
```

**Key Observations:**
- Uses `Container::Tab()` for single-screen tab switching
- Renderer pattern uses `Renderer([&] { ... })` lambda
- Content is selected via switch statement based on `selected_tab`
- Layout is vertical: header → tabs → content → footer
- Existing renderers (`RenderDashboard()`, `RenderPositions()`) return Components
- Components can be converted to Elements via `->Render()`

**Integration Points:**
- Line 163-169: Replace `Container::Tab()` with `ResizableSplitLeft()`
- Line 204-212: Replace switch statement with split pane layout
- Line 223: Replace single `content | flex` with split layout

